about.summary: Various objects to denote special meanings in python

name: sentinels
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "sentinels" %}
{% set version = "1.0.0" %}
{% set bundle = "tar.gz" %}
{% set hash_type = "sha256" %}
{% set hash_val = "7be0704d7fe1925e397e92d18669ace2f619c92b5d4eb21a89f31e026f9ff4b1" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.org/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.{{ bundle }}
  {{ hash_type }}: {{ hash_val }}

build:
  number: 1
  noarch: python
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps --ignore-installed --no-cache-dir -vvv"

requirements:
  host:
    - python
    - pip

  run:
    - python

test:
  imports:
    - sentinels

about:
  home: https://github.com/vmalloc/sentinels
  license: BSD 3-Clause
  license_file: LICENSE
  license_family: BSD
  summary: 'Various objects to denote special meanings in python'
  dev_url: https://github.com/vmalloc/sentinels

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - pmlandwehr
